      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_AgencyDashboard_AgencyEnergyUsageByFacilityStatistics",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate statistical data on energy usage by facilities within a specified agency. It calculates the number of facilities that account for a significant portion of the agency's total energy usage and provides insights into the energy consumption of the top facilities. The procedure uses temporary tables and common table expressions to aggregate and analyze energy usage data from various tables, ultimately returning a summary of energy usage statistics."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including data retrieval, aggregation, and conditional logic. It uses temporary tables, window functions, and joins, which add to its complexity. However, it does not involve highly complex algorithms or recursive logic, keeping it at a medium complexity level."
        }
      ]
    },
